1
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:40,600
Hey, buddy

2
00:01:42,880 --> 00:01:43,760
Thanks a lot

3
00:01:49,840 --> 00:01:50,560
How much?

4
00:01:51,280 --> 00:01:52,000
How much is it?

5
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:53,120
One yuan, just one

6
00:01:53,680 --> 00:01:54,320
Thanks

7
00:01:59,320 --> 00:02:00,880
Uncle Daren, off to work?

8
00:02:01,760 --> 00:02:03,120
Afu, you go on ahead

9
00:02:03,120 --> 00:02:03,720
I'm waiting for someone

10
00:02:03,720 --> 00:02:04,320
Okay

11
00:02:04,320 --> 00:02:05,080
See you in a bit

12
00:02:05,080 --> 00:02:05,400
Sure thing

13
00:02:10,240 --> 00:02:11,040
Daren

14
00:02:11,320 --> 00:02:12,400
Am I late?

15
00:02:12,400 --> 00:02:13,280
No, you're not

16
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:14,400
Put this on first

17
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:15,440
What is this thing?

18
00:02:15,680 --> 00:02:16,800
This is your work ticket

19
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:18,400
Wear it and you can find work

20
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:19,080
Got it

21
00:02:20,680 --> 00:02:21,320
How do I...

22
00:02:21,320 --> 00:02:22,080
How does this go on?

23
00:02:22,680 --> 00:02:23,480
Tighten it up

24
00:02:23,480 --> 00:02:24,200
Okay

25
00:02:26,880 --> 00:02:28,360
What kind of work can I do?

26
00:02:29,160 --> 00:02:30,960
Whatever you're told to do, you do

27
00:02:31,320 --> 00:02:32,120
Fine

28
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:33,160
As long as it's not illegal

29
00:02:33,160 --> 00:02:34,560
I can do any damn thing

30
00:02:34,560 --> 00:02:36,080
I can take any hardship

31
00:02:37,760 --> 00:02:40,200
Here, eat your breakfast first

32
00:02:40,600 --> 00:02:42,160
A full belly means strength to work

33
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:44,640
It's still hot!

34
00:02:48,520 --> 00:02:49,760
Don't rush, don't rush

35
00:02:49,760 --> 00:02:50,640
One at a time

36
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:52,200
One at a time, please

37
00:02:52,200 --> 00:02:53,120
Boss, boss

38
00:02:53,680 --> 00:02:55,200
You can haul heavy loads, right?

39
00:02:55,200 --> 00:02:55,760
Yes, I can

40
00:02:55,760 --> 00:02:56,480
Sure I can

41
00:02:56,480 --> 00:02:57,680
Then you all get ready

42
00:02:57,680 --> 00:02:58,520
Okay, come on

43
00:02:58,920 --> 00:03:00,640
Don't rush now, don't rush

44
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:03,040
Why are so many people looking for work?

45
00:03:03,880 --> 00:03:05,200
It's like this every day

46
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:14,200
Some things, you know...

47
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:16,680
you're better off not knowing

48
00:03:16,680 --> 00:03:17,920
Curiosity killed the cat

49
00:03:17,920 --> 00:03:20,240
I'm afraid you couldn't handle it.

50
00:03:20,240 --> 00:03:22,440
It's a big world, full of strange things.

51
00:03:22,440 --> 00:03:23,600
As long as you dare to tell me

52
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:25,640
I'll dare to believe it

53
00:03:25,640 --> 00:03:26,920
Alright, once I tell you

54
00:03:28,080 --> 00:03:30,320
you have to keep your lips sealed

55
00:03:31,920 --> 00:03:32,800
I promise

56
00:03:33,560 --> 00:03:34,800
If I break my word

57
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:36,080
may lightning strike me down

58
00:03:44,840 --> 00:03:45,720
That last one doesn't count

59
00:03:46,240 --> 00:03:47,040
Let's do it again

60
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:14,280
Eight years ago

61
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:16,280
after my old man passed away

62
00:04:17,840 --> 00:04:20,760
touching a relic connects my five senses

63
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:24,240
I can see and hear

64
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:27,160
what happened to the deceased when alive

65
00:04:27,640 --> 00:04:28,960
I can even feel

66
00:04:28,960 --> 00:04:30,840
their joys and sorrows at that moment

67
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:32,360
It's kind of

68
00:04:32,360 --> 00:04:33,800
a bit like dreaming

69
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:36,320
From my view it's like filming a movie

70
00:04:37,120 --> 00:04:38,640
You don't have a fever

71
00:04:38,640 --> 00:04:40,240
So why are you talking nonsense?

72
00:04:41,640 --> 00:04:42,960
Fine, don't believe me

73
00:04:42,960 --> 00:04:44,120
It sounds absurd

74
00:04:44,120 --> 00:04:44,760
but

75
00:04:44,760 --> 00:04:45,840
I believe you

76
00:04:52,640 --> 00:04:53,920
I wonder if it's connected

77
00:04:53,920 --> 00:04:55,320
to when I hit my head back then

78
00:04:55,320 --> 00:04:57,560
Maybe stuff in your brain got jumbled up

79
00:04:57,560 --> 00:04:59,760
and then recombined

80
00:04:59,760 --> 00:05:00,960
giving you superpowers

81
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:05,320
Are all you art students this abstract?

82
00:05:06,120 --> 00:05:07,720
Because your five senses connect

83
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:10,720
that's why your writing hits so hard

84
00:05:10,720 --> 00:05:11,560
Come on, man

85
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:13,600
I graduated in Chinese Literature

86
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:15,760
Stop doubting my professional skills.

87
00:05:15,760 --> 00:05:16,520
Okay, okay, okay

88
00:05:16,520 --> 00:05:17,840
Just hear me out

89
00:05:17,840 --> 00:05:19,400
Given that you have this ability

90
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:22,920
you're destined for the funeral business!

91
00:05:23,920 --> 00:05:25,160
You, me

92
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:26,640
teaming up with my sister

93
00:05:26,840 --> 00:05:29,440
we could definitely make Xiaoxitian huge

94
00:05:29,960 --> 00:05:30,960
All this talk

95
00:05:31,720 --> 00:05:32,640
you're trying to keep me here

96
00:05:36,320 --> 00:05:37,120
I know

97
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:38,840
your heart isn't in this

98
00:05:38,840 --> 00:05:41,000
I can't wake a person pretending to sleep

99
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:43,440
nor hold onto a heart that wants to leave

100
00:05:44,200 --> 00:05:45,440
You got it right

101
00:05:45,440 --> 00:05:47,280
Clear-headed as they come, kid

102
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:54,000
Oh right

103
00:05:54,440 --> 00:05:55,920
Do you have any other powers?

104
00:05:55,920 --> 00:05:57,040
Like what?

105
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:58,760
Walking through walls

106
00:05:58,760 --> 00:05:59,880
Hypnosis

107
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:00,920
Telekinesis

108
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:01,680
Are you crazy?

109
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:06,840
Friends walk through life together

110
00:06:06,840 --> 00:06:10,360
those days will never come again

111
00:06:10,360 --> 00:06:14,040
One word, a whole lifetime

112
00:06:14,400 --> 00:06:15,400
Kneel

113
00:06:22,200 --> 00:06:23,960
Heaven above,

114
00:06:24,520 --> 00:06:25,720
earth below,

115
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:26,920
I, Zhou Fang,

116
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:28,440
I, Chen Xiaofang,

117
00:06:28,440 --> 00:06:31,840
ask not to be born on the same day,

118
00:06:31,840 --> 00:06:34,880
but to die on the same day...

119
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:40,560
Hey, we don't say that word in our shop.

120
00:06:41,520 --> 00:06:42,800
It really jinxes things.

121
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:44,600
I won't say it.

122
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:45,760
I won't, I won't.

123
00:06:46,720 --> 00:06:47,800
But Xiaofang,

124
00:06:48,400 --> 00:06:52,320
you have to promise me one thing.

125
00:06:52,520 --> 00:06:57,320
You have to go before me.

126
00:06:57,320 --> 00:07:01,000
Because if I die before you,

127
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:03,560
leaving you in someone else's care,

128
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:05,680
I couldn't rest easy.

129
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:11,080
I'll go after you.

130
00:07:11,840 --> 00:07:12,800
Why, you ask?

131
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:15,960
Because you're too much of a fool.

132
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:19,040
Leaving you with someone else worries me.

133
00:07:19,040 --> 00:07:21,120
No way, you go first.

134
00:07:21,760 --> 00:07:22,720
You go first.

135
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:24,280
You go first.

136
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:27,000
You die first.

137
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:28,640
You die first.

138
00:07:28,640 --> 00:07:29,560
You die first.

139
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:30,440
You die first.

140
00:07:30,440 --> 00:07:31,400
You die first.

141
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:32,160
You die first.

142
00:07:32,160 --> 00:07:33,120
You die first.

143
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:33,800
You die first.

144
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:34,760
You die first.

145
00:07:34,760 --> 00:07:35,680
You die first.

146
00:07:39,320 --> 00:07:40,360
Get up, get up.

147
00:07:40,360 --> 00:07:41,280
All right, all right.

148
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:42,520
Easy now, easy.

149
00:07:42,520 --> 00:07:44,680
What are you two doing this late at night?

150
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:46,000
Brother-in-law,

151
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,000
I'm just so moved.

152
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:49,840
I'm not drunk, I can still drink.

153
00:07:50,640 --> 00:07:51,440
Okay, okay.

154
00:07:51,440 --> 00:07:52,920
There's serious business tomorrow.

155
00:07:52,920 --> 00:07:54,240
Head home now.

156
00:07:55,520 --> 00:07:56,160
Right.

157
00:07:56,160 --> 00:07:57,360
Serious business.

158
00:07:57,360 --> 00:07:58,440
Then I'll head home first.

159
00:07:58,440 --> 00:08:02,800
Friends walk through life together,

160
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:06,440
those days will come no more...

161
00:08:06,440 --> 00:08:07,680
Enough.

162
00:08:08,400 --> 00:08:08,960
He's already gone.

163
00:08:08,960 --> 00:08:09,720
Stop putting on an act.

164
00:08:10,320 --> 00:08:12,320
I'm not acting.

165
00:08:12,320 --> 00:08:13,920
I'm genuinely drinking to forget.

166
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:17,440
Yiran, I'm getting married tomorrow.

167
00:08:17,440 --> 00:08:19,080
I'm really anxious.

168
00:08:20,120 --> 00:08:22,320
What are you anxious about?

169
00:08:22,320 --> 00:08:23,720
You two know each other inside out.

170
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:25,040
It's a love marathon.

171
00:08:25,040 --> 00:08:26,240
So what's there to worry about?

172
00:08:28,200 --> 00:08:29,400
You have no idea.

173
00:08:30,120 --> 00:08:31,280
They all say

174
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:34,800
marriage is the grave of love.

175
00:08:36,240 --> 00:08:38,240
I'm really scared that once I marry,

176
00:08:38,720 --> 00:08:40,800
a family brings a burden,

177
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:45,160
and Zhou Fang and I will end up in the grave.

178
00:08:46,560 --> 00:08:47,600
Bah, bah, bah, knock on wood.

179
00:08:48,920 --> 00:08:49,640
Bah, bah, bah.

180
00:08:49,960 --> 00:08:51,120
It's such a wonderful thing.

181
00:08:51,120 --> 00:08:52,720
Why go on about all this nonsense?

182
00:08:55,280 --> 00:08:56,120
Oh, right.

183
00:08:56,120 --> 00:09:00,720
What were you and my brother doing alone?

184
00:09:00,720 --> 00:09:02,480
I didn't even call you two out.

185
00:09:02,920 --> 00:09:04,360
It's not what you think.

186
00:09:04,760 --> 00:09:06,640
We were discussing the five-sense link.

187
00:09:06,640 --> 00:09:07,400
Chen Baixi!

188
00:09:08,760 --> 00:09:10,480
That mouth of yours...

189
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:13,040
He, he...

190
00:09:13,040 --> 00:09:14,400
The two of us were just saying...

191
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:18,000
talking about how to pay off debt faster.

192
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:18,600
Paying off debt?

193
00:09:19,120 --> 00:09:21,920
After all, 200,000 is no small sum.

194
00:09:21,920 --> 00:09:22,600
We said, split it into five payments.

195
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:23,760
Brother,

196
00:09:24,120 --> 00:09:25,720
do you have feelings for Yiran?

197
00:09:30,040 --> 00:09:30,840
Come on, tell me.

198
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:32,360
No way.

199
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:35,080
You know me well.

200
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:36,000
Impossible.

201
00:09:37,800 --> 00:09:39,960
I know you too well, that's why I said it.

202
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:41,320
This acting of yours...

203
00:09:41,920 --> 00:09:42,840
Your face is all red.

204
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:44,000
You've got it wrong.

205
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:44,960
I've just had a bit too much to drink.

206
00:09:44,960 --> 00:09:45,600
Xiaofang,

207
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:47,080
listen, tomorrow's a big day.

208
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:48,440
I'll go with you to the registry office.

209
00:09:48,440 --> 00:09:50,760
Let's get a good rest tonight, okay?

210
00:09:50,760 --> 00:09:51,400
Come on.

211
00:09:51,720 --> 00:09:52,880
I'll go pack up.

212
00:09:54,040 --> 00:09:54,960
I'll grab a bag.

213
00:10:16,120 --> 00:10:17,360
Well then

214
00:10:17,360 --> 00:10:18,160
The two of us guardians

215
00:10:18,160 --> 00:10:19,200
won't be going in there with you two

216
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:21,320
Go on

217
00:10:22,680 --> 00:10:23,320
Let's go

218
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:44,680
Here.

219
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:45,360
This is yours.

220
00:10:45,360 --> 00:10:46,160
And this is yours.

221
00:10:46,160 --> 00:10:46,640
Thank you.

222
00:10:46,640 --> 00:10:47,360
Thank you.

223
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:50,160
Share in our joy.

224
00:10:51,760 --> 00:10:52,560
Good things come in pairs.

225
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:53,760
Thank you!

226
00:10:53,760 --> 00:10:55,400
May you two be forever united.

227
00:10:55,400 --> 00:10:56,240
And have a child soon.

228
00:10:56,240 --> 00:10:57,080
Thank you.

229
00:10:57,080 --> 00:10:57,920
Thanks.

230
00:10:57,920 --> 00:10:58,440
Let's go.

231
00:11:06,640 --> 00:11:07,680
You scared me!

232
00:11:07,680 --> 00:11:08,360
You two are way over the top.

233
00:11:08,360 --> 00:11:10,320
Congratulations on your wedding!

234
00:11:11,480 --> 00:11:12,560
Thank you both!

235
00:11:12,560 --> 00:11:14,560
Today you're officially licensed.

236
00:11:14,560 --> 00:11:16,200
We've got to celebrate.

237
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:17,640
Three-star Michelin, how about it?

238
00:11:17,760 --> 00:11:18,800
Perfect!

239
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:20,440
You stole our Xiaofang away,

240
00:11:20,440 --> 00:11:21,760
so we're gonna bleed you dry.

241
00:11:21,760 --> 00:11:22,920
Zhou Fang!

242
00:11:23,880 --> 00:11:24,640
Dad.

243
00:11:24,640 --> 00:11:25,440
Uncle.

244
00:11:25,440 --> 00:11:26,160
Hello, sir.

245
00:11:26,160 --> 00:11:26,920
Zhou Fang,

246
00:11:26,920 --> 00:11:29,360
do you even care about me, your father?

247
00:11:30,160 --> 00:11:31,360
When did I ever agree

248
00:11:31,360 --> 00:11:33,000
to you marrying into the funeral trade?

249
00:11:33,160 --> 00:11:33,520
You...

250
00:11:34,800 --> 00:11:37,520
you even dared to steal the family register!

251
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:39,240
If Wumei hadn't told me,

252
00:11:39,760 --> 00:11:41,160
were you planning to defy me completely?

253
00:11:43,400 --> 00:11:45,240
Didn't you tell me your dad agreed?

254
00:11:46,160 --> 00:11:47,920
Well, obviously he didn't.

255
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:50,200
I was just so eager to marry you,

256
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:51,320
that's why I snuck out the register.

257
00:11:51,320 --> 00:11:52,760
Who knew you don't even need it anymore?

258
00:11:53,840 --> 00:11:54,800
Sir.

259
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:56,160
Why don't we talk somewhere else?

260
00:11:56,400 --> 00:11:57,600
This is a family matter.

261
00:11:58,200 --> 00:11:59,160
It's none of your business.

262
00:12:02,680 --> 00:12:04,640
If you dare go through with this wedding,

263
00:12:05,640 --> 00:12:07,720
I'll disown you as my son.

264
00:12:08,840 --> 00:12:09,720
Then disown me.

265
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:13,440
We're already legally married anyway.

266
00:12:13,920 --> 00:12:15,120
You little brat!

267
00:12:15,120 --> 00:12:15,960
How dare you!

268
00:12:15,960 --> 00:12:16,680
Mr. Zhou.

269
00:12:16,680 --> 00:12:17,800
There's no need for this, come on.

270
00:12:19,040 --> 00:12:20,960
Don't think I can't rein you in.

271
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:23,280
I'll freeze every one of your cards.

272
00:12:23,280 --> 00:12:24,920
Let's see how many days you last.

273
00:12:24,920 --> 00:12:27,040
Even if you freeze all my cards,

274
00:12:27,160 --> 00:12:29,120
I'm still going to marry Xiaofang.

275
00:12:29,240 --> 00:12:30,040
You...

276
00:12:41,400 --> 00:12:42,160
Dad

277
00:12:44,880 --> 00:12:45,800
What'll it take

278
00:12:46,480 --> 00:12:47,840
for you to leave my son?

279
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:49,960
Name your price.

280
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:54,920
Sir, this really isn't right.

281
00:12:55,320 --> 00:12:57,360
Dad, this won't work.

282
00:12:57,360 --> 00:12:58,480
Xiaofang is not like that at all.

283
00:12:58,480 --> 00:12:59,360
Fine then.

284
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:15,920
You.

285
00:13:23,120 --> 00:13:24,840
On this card,

286
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:26,160
there's a million.

287
00:13:26,440 --> 00:13:28,160
Leave my son right now.

288
00:13:29,280 --> 00:13:31,560
I was only going to ask for 100 grand.

289
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:33,400
Didn't expect him to be so generous.

290
00:13:33,400 --> 00:13:35,120
A whole million, just like that.

291
00:13:36,320 --> 00:13:38,080
Guess I was still too naive.

292
00:13:40,720 --> 00:13:42,040
Just wait, sir.

293
00:13:42,040 --> 00:13:43,920
I'll do exactly as you wish right now.

294
00:13:43,920 --> 00:13:45,520
Xiaofang! Xiaofang!

295
00:13:48,680 --> 00:13:49,600
Divorce.

296
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:57,840
You two just got married.

297
00:13:57,840 --> 00:13:58,760
None of your business. I want a divorce.

298
00:13:58,760 --> 00:13:59,640
The faster, the better.

299
00:14:01,320 --> 00:14:03,640
Think it through next time you marry.

300
00:14:03,640 --> 00:14:04,720
This isn't playing house!

301
00:14:04,720 --> 00:14:05,840
There won't be a next time.

302
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:08,360
Sorry.

303
00:14:08,360 --> 00:14:09,120
Sorry to trouble you.

304
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:11,840
That was faster than ordering takeout.

305
00:14:12,840 --> 00:14:13,760
Fingerprint here.

306
00:14:13,760 --> 00:14:15,080
There's a 30-day cooling-off period.

307
00:14:15,240 --> 00:14:16,880
If you change your mind, you can withdraw it.

308
00:14:17,120 --> 00:14:18,240
I'm changing my mind right now.

309
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:25,120
Xiaofang.

310
00:14:25,360 --> 00:14:26,800
Press it, for me.

311
00:14:51,920 --> 00:14:52,640
This...

312
00:14:59,280 --> 00:15:00,200
Xiaofang

313
00:15:01,040 --> 00:15:02,640
I'm dreaming right now, aren't I?

314
00:15:06,440 --> 00:15:07,240
Zhou Fang

315
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:08,960
From now on

316
00:15:09,280 --> 00:15:11,160
you go your way

317
00:15:12,120 --> 00:15:13,640
and I'll go mine

318
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:15,600
Let's just leave each other be

319
00:15:26,760 --> 00:15:27,560
Xiaofang

320
00:15:29,560 --> 00:15:30,600
I'll go check on her

321
00:15:35,960 --> 00:15:36,960
It's fine

322
00:15:36,960 --> 00:15:38,000
We're the most fickle

323
00:15:38,320 --> 00:15:38,760
No

324
00:15:39,040 --> 00:15:40,040
It's women

325
00:15:40,040 --> 00:15:40,800
Women are the most fickle

326
00:15:40,800 --> 00:15:42,200
Xu Wumei, just shut up

327
00:15:46,600 --> 00:15:48,240
Chen Xiaofang just loves money

328
00:15:48,800 --> 00:15:49,840
In her heart

329
00:15:50,120 --> 00:15:51,280
this one million

330
00:15:51,320 --> 00:15:52,320
matters more than you

331
00:15:52,360 --> 00:15:53,240
She's not like that

332
00:16:03,960 --> 00:16:04,840
Xiaofang

333
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:09,280
Sis

334
00:16:09,640 --> 00:16:11,160
What kind of act was that just now?

335
00:16:12,080 --> 00:16:12,760
Do you have any idea

336
00:16:12,760 --> 00:16:14,480
what happens if Dad finds out about this?

337
00:16:14,480 --> 00:16:15,120
Bro

338
00:16:15,720 --> 00:16:16,920
Yeah, I love Zhou Fang

339
00:16:17,440 --> 00:16:18,800
but I love money even more!

340
00:16:19,120 --> 00:16:20,080
Do you have any idea

341
00:16:20,080 --> 00:16:22,440
how many funerals our family has to run

342
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:23,800
just to earn that one million?

343
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:27,520
Exactly

344
00:16:28,120 --> 00:16:29,400
You're a little rich lady now

345
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:30,760
A millionaire!

346
00:16:30,760 --> 00:16:31,520
Who needs a man?

347
00:16:32,600 --> 00:16:33,800
Call that talking her out of it?

348
00:16:34,320 --> 00:16:35,120
Yeah

349
00:16:35,600 --> 00:16:37,520
Score a 30-day divorce cooling-off period

350
00:16:37,520 --> 00:16:38,880
and pocket a free one million too!

351
00:16:40,160 --> 00:16:40,960
Let's go!

352
00:16:51,520 --> 00:16:52,520
I'll go find Zhou Fang.

353
00:16:53,840 --> 00:16:54,840
I'll come with you.

354
00:16:55,440 --> 00:16:57,160
You've gone too far, Zhou Fang.

355
00:16:57,160 --> 00:16:57,920
What were you thinking?

356
00:16:57,920 --> 00:16:59,120
Do you even have a brain?

357
00:16:59,120 --> 00:16:59,840
What kind of problem is this?

358
00:16:59,840 --> 00:17:01,000
This is a matter of principle.

359
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:01,800
To put it bluntly,

360
00:17:01,800 --> 00:17:03,400
this is marriage fraud, you know that?

361
00:17:03,400 --> 00:17:04,040
Okay, okay, okay.

362
00:17:04,040 --> 00:17:05,200
Sit down first, sit down.

363
00:17:05,200 --> 00:17:06,240
Just sit down.

364
00:17:07,120 --> 00:17:08,760
I didn't mean to deceive her.

365
00:17:08,760 --> 00:17:10,680
I just wanted so badly to marry her.

366
00:17:11,320 --> 00:17:12,800
The way your dad acted today,

367
00:17:12,800 --> 00:17:14,200
if my sister had married into that family,

368
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:16,000
who knows how badly she'd be bullied.

369
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:16,960
Good thing they divorced.

370
00:17:18,040 --> 00:17:19,800
How could I ever let her get bullied?

371
00:17:20,520 --> 00:17:22,560
You two are my friends, after all.

372
00:17:22,720 --> 00:17:24,120
Could you at least comfort me a little?

373
00:17:24,120 --> 00:17:26,200
Divorced on my wedding day, seriously.

374
00:17:26,200 --> 00:17:27,800
What did I do to deserve this?

375
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:28,720
What sin did I commit?

376
00:17:28,720 --> 00:17:30,280
You brought this on yourself.

377
00:17:30,760 --> 00:17:31,720
A dreamy start,

378
00:17:31,720 --> 00:17:32,320
a nightmare ending.

379
00:17:32,320 --> 00:17:33,280
You totally deserve it.

380
00:17:33,800 --> 00:17:34,600
It's a pretty good ending, though.

381
00:17:34,600 --> 00:17:35,520
I'd call it a perfect ending.

382
00:17:35,520 --> 00:17:36,360
Everyone's happy.

383
00:17:36,360 --> 00:17:37,520
Good thing Xiaofang didn't stay with you,

384
00:17:37,520 --> 00:17:38,760
right, Mr. Award-Winning Actor?

385
00:17:38,760 --> 00:17:39,560
Fair enough.

386
00:17:41,840 --> 00:17:43,120
Yiran, you...

387
00:17:43,600 --> 00:17:45,040
How can you be like this?

388
00:17:45,040 --> 00:17:46,600
Comforting one while insulting another.

389
00:17:49,320 --> 00:17:50,320
Brother-in-law,

390
00:17:50,320 --> 00:17:51,720
try to think of something.

391
00:17:53,560 --> 00:17:54,600
Don't call me that.

392
00:17:55,440 --> 00:17:57,120
Xiaofang's always been headstrong.

393
00:17:57,120 --> 00:17:58,720
Once she decides on something,

394
00:17:58,720 --> 00:17:59,920
she usually won't change her mind.

395
00:18:02,640 --> 00:18:04,800
But you two just got divorced.

396
00:18:04,800 --> 00:18:07,040
There's a 30-day cooling-off period.

397
00:18:07,520 --> 00:18:10,520
Maybe things could turn around.

398
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:14,040
Brother-in-law, you're right.

399
00:18:14,840 --> 00:18:16,800
I still have that cooling-off period.

400
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:18,800
After all, I just got married today too.

401
00:18:18,800 --> 00:18:20,400
Stop thinking about marriage or divorce

402
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:21,440
or cooling off or whatever.

403
00:18:21,440 --> 00:18:22,720
You just calm down first.

404
00:18:22,720 --> 00:18:24,120
Deal with your dad before anything else.

405
00:18:24,120 --> 00:18:25,120
Young Master Zhou.

406
00:18:26,600 --> 00:18:27,720
I think, you know,

407
00:18:27,720 --> 00:18:28,720
Yiran's right.

408
00:18:29,360 --> 00:18:30,520
Some things, you know,

409
00:18:30,520 --> 00:18:31,720
are just like these skewers.

410
00:18:31,720 --> 00:18:33,120
Wait too long and they go cold.

411
00:18:36,640 --> 00:18:38,000
Uncle Daren, you're right.

412
00:18:38,640 --> 00:18:41,000
Some things really can't wait.

413
00:18:41,840 --> 00:18:43,520
I'll go back right now and handle my dad.

414
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:45,040
Here, Uncle Daren.

415
00:18:45,040 --> 00:18:45,960
This is for the meal.

416
00:18:47,160 --> 00:18:47,920
You guys eat, go on.

417
00:18:47,920 --> 00:18:48,600
I won't eat then.

418
00:18:48,720 --> 00:18:49,440
No, no.

419
00:18:49,720 --> 00:18:50,680
This can wait.

420
00:18:50,680 --> 00:18:51,520
It can wait.

421
00:18:51,920 --> 00:18:53,160
Then I'll keep it for you.

422
00:18:54,360 --> 00:18:55,240
Just put it away, quick.

423
00:18:55,240 --> 00:18:55,600
That's too much money.

424
00:18:55,600 --> 00:18:56,120
I know, I know.

425
00:18:56,120 --> 00:18:58,080
I promised to roast him a whole lamb.

426
00:18:58,080 --> 00:18:58,720
Forget the roast lamb, Uncle Daren.

427
00:18:58,720 --> 00:19:00,600
Next time I'll roast you a whole cow.

428
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:01,480
He doesn't deserve it.

429
00:19:01,480 --> 00:19:02,120
No roast for him.

430
00:19:02,120 --> 00:19:03,120
All right.

431
00:19:12,800 --> 00:19:13,800
Have some skewers.

432
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:15,120
I don't want any.

433
00:19:17,320 --> 00:19:18,720
Eat up, they're getting cold.

434
00:19:19,560 --> 00:19:20,640
What's wrong with you?

435
00:19:23,800 --> 00:19:26,160
Those Zhous are pushing us around!

436
00:19:26,440 --> 00:19:28,240
I'm going over to the Zhous right now

437
00:19:28,240 --> 00:19:29,160
to demand an explanation.

438
00:19:30,040 --> 00:19:30,800
Dad.

439
00:19:31,520 --> 00:19:32,640
Let me ask you something.

440
00:19:34,720 --> 00:19:35,760
How much savings do you have?

441
00:19:37,120 --> 00:19:38,920
At a time like this,

442
00:19:38,920 --> 00:19:40,720
why are you asking that?

443
00:19:40,720 --> 00:19:42,160
Be honest, how much savings do you have?

444
00:19:43,400 --> 00:19:45,200
I lent your brother 200,000.

445
00:19:46,160 --> 00:19:48,200
So I've got about 300,000 left.

446
00:19:48,360 --> 00:19:49,160
See?

447
00:19:49,920 --> 00:19:53,240
You slaved half your life for 500,000.

448
00:19:53,560 --> 00:19:55,480
Today, one sentence earned me a million.

449
00:19:58,160 --> 00:19:59,840
Oh, you.

450
00:20:00,360 --> 00:20:02,800
This isn't about money.

451
00:20:03,520 --> 00:20:05,640
This is about your marriage.

452
00:20:05,920 --> 00:20:08,520
I won't let you get pushed around.

453
00:20:09,440 --> 00:20:10,880
Dad.

454
00:20:11,880 --> 00:20:13,880
Do I look like someone who gets pushed around?

455
00:20:14,440 --> 00:20:15,920
If I don't push the Zhous around,

456
00:20:15,920 --> 00:20:17,640
they should count themselves lucky.

457
00:20:21,120 --> 00:20:22,000
My child,

458
00:20:22,640 --> 00:20:23,800
you have to remember,

459
00:20:24,280 --> 00:20:27,240
when it comes to marriage,

460
00:20:27,240 --> 00:20:28,960
never settle for less than you deserve.

461
00:20:31,680 --> 00:20:32,560
Don't worry.

462
00:20:33,320 --> 00:20:34,600
As long as your dad's around,

463
00:20:35,160 --> 00:20:37,960
I'll never let you suffer one bit.

464
00:20:42,160 --> 00:20:44,320
Dad, I know.

465
00:20:45,080 --> 00:20:46,800
I'm just afraid

466
00:20:46,800 --> 00:20:48,480
you'll think that I

467
00:20:48,480 --> 00:20:49,880
married in and got mistreated,

468
00:20:49,880 --> 00:20:51,720
and your health isn't good either.

469
00:20:52,640 --> 00:20:53,640
I know.

470
00:20:55,360 --> 00:20:57,400
Our family's in this line of work,

471
00:20:58,960 --> 00:21:02,360
and the Zhous find it unlucky.

472
00:21:04,240 --> 00:21:07,040
I also know I'm old now,

473
00:21:09,440 --> 00:21:10,880
and I'm not good for much.

474
00:21:12,360 --> 00:21:15,880
So I've never meddled in your marriages.

475
00:21:17,320 --> 00:21:18,880
But I do hope

476
00:21:18,880 --> 00:21:20,560
you can both find

477
00:21:20,560 --> 00:21:23,600
someone you truly love.

478
00:21:24,480 --> 00:21:25,880
Dad, don't worry.

479
00:21:25,880 --> 00:21:27,560
I know what I'm doing.

480
00:21:55,880 --> 00:21:56,560
Dad

481
00:21:57,640 --> 00:21:58,880
Just let me explain

482
00:21:59,560 --> 00:22:01,080
It was wrong to steal the family register

483
00:22:01,360 --> 00:22:03,800
But I have to marry Chen Xiaofang

484
00:22:04,680 --> 00:22:06,360
You're gonna be the death of me

485
00:22:07,600 --> 00:22:08,240
Let's go

486
00:22:08,800 --> 00:22:09,560
Dad

487
00:22:11,960 --> 00:22:12,640
Dad

488
00:22:24,400 --> 00:22:25,760
The damn weather forecast

489
00:22:25,760 --> 00:22:26,960
isn't accurate at all

490
00:22:27,440 --> 00:22:28,760
Such heavy rain

491
00:22:29,440 --> 00:22:30,560
Where'd you go?

492
00:22:30,560 --> 00:22:31,840
Coming back this late

493
00:22:36,200 --> 00:22:37,360
What are you doing?

494
00:22:37,360 --> 00:22:38,240
Did you miss me?

495
00:22:38,240 --> 00:22:39,200
You care about me?

496
00:22:41,560 --> 00:22:44,160
I'd better just worry about myself

497
00:22:44,440 --> 00:22:45,920
Being jobless isn't scary

498
00:22:45,920 --> 00:22:48,520
What's scary is staying jobless forever

499
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:01,320
Here.

500
00:23:04,080 --> 00:23:06,960
It's the same one you lost.

501
00:23:07,360 --> 00:23:09,080
I bought it at the official store.

502
00:23:09,840 --> 00:23:11,000
This model costs over 2,000.

503
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:12,080
Where'd you get the money for it?

504
00:23:13,120 --> 00:23:14,480
Don't look down on me.

505
00:23:15,160 --> 00:23:17,320
I earned it doing odd jobs lately.

506
00:23:18,080 --> 00:23:20,360
What odd job pays over 2,000 so fast?

507
00:23:21,360 --> 00:23:22,680
I've got two hands and two feet.

508
00:23:22,680 --> 00:23:23,920
I didn't steal or rob anyone.

509
00:23:23,920 --> 00:23:26,040
I'd never do anything illegal.

510
00:23:26,040 --> 00:23:26,880
Use it, don't worry.

511
00:23:27,200 --> 00:23:28,000
And one more thing.

512
00:23:28,480 --> 00:23:30,240
The debts I owe, I'll pay off myself.

513
00:23:30,240 --> 00:23:31,360
Stay out of it.

514
00:23:32,560 --> 00:23:33,960
That bankbook of yours,

515
00:23:33,960 --> 00:23:35,720
I put it under your pillow.

516
00:23:37,440 --> 00:23:39,320
Wu Huilian, listen to me.

517
00:23:39,320 --> 00:23:41,240
Those shady jobs from Auntie Juan,

518
00:23:41,240 --> 00:23:42,680
you really can't take them anymore.

519
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:45,800
You hear me?

520
00:23:49,160 --> 00:23:50,920
What do you mean, shady jobs?

521
00:23:51,560 --> 00:23:53,440
I'm in great shape right now.

522
00:23:53,440 --> 00:23:54,600
The moment money sees me,

523
00:23:54,600 --> 00:23:55,680
it comes flying straight at me.

524
00:23:55,680 --> 00:23:57,160
It chases after me, you know?

525
00:23:59,480 --> 00:24:00,360
Go take a shower first.

526
00:24:00,360 --> 00:24:01,320
Don't catch a cold.

527
00:25:01,440 --> 00:25:02,680
Wu Huilian

528
00:25:19,320 --> 00:25:21,680
Don't worry

529
00:25:24,920 --> 00:25:26,760
Where'd she go this early?

530
00:25:27,840 --> 00:25:29,920
Did she get conned by some quack again?

531
00:25:38,360 --> 00:25:39,160
Dad

532
00:25:40,480 --> 00:25:41,280
Don't worry

533
00:25:41,800 --> 00:25:43,160
I'll keep an eye on her

534
00:25:44,200 --> 00:25:46,400
She just got out and doesn't know a thing

535
00:25:46,640 --> 00:25:48,720
And she's been out of touch for so many years

536
00:25:48,720 --> 00:25:50,600
I really don't want to deal with her

537
00:25:50,600 --> 00:25:52,840
But, for your sake

538
00:25:53,440 --> 00:25:55,240
I'll grit my teeth and

539
00:25:56,200 --> 00:25:57,240
keep an eye on her, I guess

540
00:25:57,760 --> 00:25:59,400
Can't just let her get scammed, right?

541
00:26:14,680 --> 00:26:16,280
Waking up early ruins the whole day

542
00:26:29,240 --> 00:26:30,920
Something's off here.

543
00:26:30,920 --> 00:26:32,480
Something's off about this Wu Huilian.

544
00:26:37,320 --> 00:26:38,880
Aren't I just asking for trouble?

545
00:27:23,080 --> 00:27:24,400
Why aren't you asleep yet?

546
00:27:26,960 --> 00:27:28,720
Where'd you go? Coming home this late.

547
00:27:30,240 --> 00:27:31,960
Went to play mahjong.

548
00:27:33,120 --> 00:27:34,600
Wanted to win some money off them.

549
00:27:35,000 --> 00:27:36,840
But my luck today was just terrible.

550
00:27:36,840 --> 00:27:38,240
Downright cursed.

551
00:27:38,240 --> 00:27:39,120
I'm gonna take a shower.

552
00:27:39,120 --> 00:27:40,080
Wash off the bad luck.

553
00:27:40,760 --> 00:27:41,520
Hold on, hold on.

554
00:27:41,520 --> 00:27:41,960
Wait a second.

555
00:27:41,960 --> 00:27:42,560
You stand right there.

556
00:27:43,080 --> 00:27:43,880
What for?

557
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:48,080
What is it now?

558
00:27:50,680 --> 00:27:51,760
What's that smell?

559
00:27:51,760 --> 00:27:53,080
You reek of perfume mixed with stink.

560
00:27:53,080 --> 00:27:54,000
It's suffocating!

561
00:27:55,600 --> 00:27:56,680
That damn Zhang Lijuan.

562
00:27:57,680 --> 00:27:58,760
She sprayed that perfume all over me.

563
00:27:58,760 --> 00:27:59,480
Stinks to high heaven.

564
00:28:01,400 --> 00:28:02,800
What are you staring at?

565
00:28:03,800 --> 00:28:04,840
What happened to your hand?

566
00:28:05,640 --> 00:28:06,280
This?

567
00:28:07,520 --> 00:28:09,480
I was playing mahjong today.

568
00:28:09,480 --> 00:28:10,920
Those tiles were huge.

569
00:28:11,120 --> 00:28:12,840
And it was a brand-new set.

570
00:28:12,840 --> 00:28:14,160
The tiles weren't smooth at all.

571
00:28:14,160 --> 00:28:15,360
I shuffled back and forth.

572
00:28:15,720 --> 00:28:16,520
Shuffling really hard.

573
00:28:16,520 --> 00:28:18,200
And ended up scraping my hand raw.

574
00:28:18,200 --> 00:28:18,720
See?

575
00:28:18,720 --> 00:28:20,080
All from shuffling mahjong.

576
00:28:20,080 --> 00:28:21,120
Mahjong tiles made of knives?

577
00:28:21,560 --> 00:28:22,480
Razor blades on the tiles?

578
00:28:22,480 --> 00:28:24,080
Slashed your hand up like this, huh?

579
00:28:24,280 --> 00:28:25,080
Take a look yourself.

580
